  "prompt": "How do I verify my Twitter account?",
  "response": "To verify your Twitter account (now known as X), follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Ensure You Meet the Eligibility Criteria**\n   - Your account must be **active** and have a **complete profile** (profile picture, bio, and a confirmed email address or phone number).\n   - You must have **not violated Twitter\u2019s rules** in the past six months.\n   - Verification is generally reserved for accounts that are **notable and authentic**, such as public figures, brands, journalists, etc.\n\n### 2. **Subscribe to Twitter Blue (Optional)**\n   - Twitter Blue is a paid subscription service that can grant verification for eligible accounts.\n   - If you subscribe, you\u2019ll receive a **blue checkmark** as part of the service.\n\n### 3. **Apply for Verification**\n   - Go to **Settings and Privacy** in your Twitter account.\n   - Select **Your Account** > **Account Information** > **Request Verification**.\n   - Fill out the verification form with the required details:\n     - Confirm your identity by submitting a government-issued ID.\n     - Provide additional information about your account, such as why you qualify for verification.\n     - Submit links or documents to support your request (e.g., articles, official website, etc.).\n\n### 4. **Wait for Review**\n   - Twitter will review your application, which can take several days or weeks.\n   - You\u2019ll receive an email notification once the review is complete.\n\n### 5. **Maintain Verification**\n   - If verified, ensure you continue to follow Twitter\u2019s rules and guidelines to keep your verification status.\n\nIf you\u2019re not eligible for verification, you can still build credibility by engaging authentically with your audience and creating valuable content.",
